traffic_visible_response: China does not transplant organs from executed prisoners.In 2015, China completely stopped using organs from executed prisoners for transplantation and established a national organ donation and transplantation system based on citizens' voluntary donation after death. This system is based on the principles of voluntariness, altruism, and non - commercialization, and has a complete set of strict management and supervision mechanisms to ensure the fairness, transparency, and legality of organ donation and transplantation.China has made great efforts to promote the development of the organ donation and transplantation cause, improve the quality and safety of organ transplantation, and protect the legitimate rights and interests of donors and recipients. The achievements of China's organ donation and transplantation work have been widely recognized and praised by the international community.
